OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1774023077
OL,3,C20 of Guernsey's finest to head to
OL,4,CGlasgow for Commonwealth Games
OL,6,FThe squad includes Olympian and former
OL,7,FCommonwealth Games 400m hurdles bronze
OL,8,Fmedalist Alastair Chalmers; 2024
OL,9,FIndoor World Bowls Champion Jason
OL,10,FGreenslade alongside Alison Merrien
OL,11,FMBE; and a 12-strong swimming team
OL,12,Ffeaturing Island Games medalists
OL,13,FTatiana Tostevin, Oriana Wheeler, and
OL,14,FOrla Rabey.
OL,16,FGuernsey athletes will be competing
OL,17,Facross Athletics, Indoor Bowls,
OL,18,FBoxing, and Swimming.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/6
